text.__SUMMARY__: Conus sydneyensis is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae, the cone snails and their allies.Like all species within the genus Conus, these snails are predatory and venomous. They are capable of "stinging" humans, therefore live ones should not be handled at all, except by qualified federal animal control personnel.
text.Description: The size of the shell varies  between 21 mm and 50 mm.
text.Distribution: This marine species is endemic to Australia and occurs off New South Wales.
